title: Support or Leg of an Object
period: Ptolemaic Period to early Roman Period
description:
Small bronze support or leg of an object. Torso and head of Bes or Silenus terminating in circular lion foot.  Two pronged support on back of figure.
Condition: Fair. Intact but rather heavily corroded.
dimensions: 2 7/16 x diameter of base 1 in. (6.2 x 2.6 cm)
credit_line: Gift of Evangeline Wilbour Blashfield, Theodora Wilbour, and Victor Wilbour honoring the wishes of their mother, Charlotte Beebe Wilbour, as a memorial to their father, Charles Edwin Wilbour

museum_location.name: This item is not on view
